# Explanatory comments

Add **explanatory** comments (why, non-obvious intent, domain constraints) **only when someone reading the code cannot infer the full purpose and context of what the code is doing** from names, structure, and types alone.

- **Prefer** clear identifiers, small functions, and straightforward control flow over comments that restate the code.
- **Do not** add comments for obvious steps, routine API usage, or “what this line does” when it is already visible from the code.
- **Do** comment when the behavior depends on **external contracts**, **subtle ordering**, **performance or platform trade-offs**, or **non-local invariants** that are not apparent at the call site.

When in doubt, default to **no** new comment unless the missing context would reasonably cause a wrong change or misuse.

---

Generated code under `src/Codegen/` is not hand-edited; follow project codegen guidelines there instead of adding manual comments in generated files.
